    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Floating-point arithmetic is not the reals. Our bisection for &radic;2 converges to a float, not an exact real. The completeness axiom is about the mathematical structure, not any computer representation. The irrationality proof of &radic;2 is a proof by contradiction that can't be "run" in the REPL.</p>

